stepTitle: Given the height, s, of a projectile after $$t$$ seconds is $$s(t)=-16t^2+80t$$, explain the meaning of $$s(0)=0$$ and $$s(5)=0$$ in words.
answerLatex: The projectile begins at a height of $$0$$ feet and after $$5$$ seconds, is at $$0$$ feet again.
